cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about improving on-line visual object trackers using deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a meta-learning-based method to adjust deep networks for tracking, which involves optimizing the network's parameters and coefficients for fast online adaptation. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with tracking objects in real-world environments, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard benchmarks, which could also make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
